<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/51a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-23T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 23, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President, pursuant to treaty stipulations, has nominated Mr. A. J.
                            Maumus, of Louisiana, as General Receiver, and Mr. W. S. Matthews,
                            Junior, of Mississippi, as Deputy General Receiver of Customs of
                            Haiti.</p>
                        <p>Please so inform the President and state that this Government will be
                            happy to learn of his appointment of these officials.</p>
                        <p>Question of Financial Adviser receiving utmost attention of
                            Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>